is something in the way of the sensors.";i:6;s:109:"Garage door openers made after 1993 are equipped with sensors positioned on both sides of the vertical rails.";i:7;s:140:"If your garage door opener wont close and the motor unit lights blink 10 times it usually means you have a problem with your safety sensors.";i:8;s:143:"In this video from Sears PartsDirect well show you some simple fixes like checking the garage door openers alignment and clearing obstructions.";i:9;s:135:"Having your garage door light blink continuously is not only annoying its also a sign that there is something wrong with the mechanism.";i:10;s:68:"There are several reasons why your garage door opener is doing this.";i:11;s:119:"However the two most common reasons include a problem with the lock button and malfunctioning safety reversing sensors.";i:12;s:164:"The purpose of the safety sensors located on the bottom corners of your garage door is to automatically reverse your door if they detect motion underneath the door.";i:13;s:154:"If the opener cannot detect that the safety sensors are properly working or connected then the opener lights will flash and the door will refuse to close.";i:14;s:50:"MY GARAGE DOOR KEEPS REVERSING AND WILL NOT CLOSE.";i:15;s:256:"Probably the most common phone call we get in the service department is My garage door keeps reversing and I cant get it to close or My remotes wont close the door and I have to hold the wall button until the door is all the way down for it to stay closed.";i:16;s:52:"Check the connected unit close the electric circuit.";i:17;s:84:"The OPEN force limit has been activated - the door has come to a halt while opening.";i:18;s:78:"If the door has come to a halt for no obvious reason check the door mechanics.";i:19;s:85:"When the work light flashes 10 times there is a problem with the door safety sensors.";i:20;s:60:"There might be a problem in the logic board causing it also.";i:21;s:51:"Be sure the leds on the sensors are burning steady."